CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 13, 1953, pg. 10, reads: "THE WAMS! - The attractive members of the WAMS, the women's auxiliary to the Mortuary Fraternity, whose date with Joe Louis, his review at the Carousel has been changed to Oct. 18, announce that the affair will begin promptly at 9 o'clock that night, and that there will be no tickets sold at the door. There will also be no reserved tables; first come, first served.  Tickets are going fast, get yours now!  Pictured are the WAMS.  Seated: Pauline Williams and Kate Ellis.  Front row, president Adda Waters; Doralester Robinson, Jane Austin and Florida Coles.  Back row, chairman of the "Autumn Nocturne," Ardelle Douglas, and Sadye Wilborne. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eight women from WAMS [women's auxiliary to the mortuary fraternity] Club, including Pauline Williams and Kate Ellis seated; Ardelle Douglas, Adda Waters, Doralester Robinson, Jane Austin, Sadye Wilborne, and Florida Coles standing, posed in Loendi Club
